cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CY 

The paper deals with the problem of optimizing disk block storage for interaction graphs, which is a common problem in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the application domains of interaction graphs, including telecommunications, transportation, and social media, which fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper presents ILP formulations and greedy heuristic approaches for partitioning disk blocks, which are related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CY (Computational Geometry).
